        "text": "Adverse effects in BACE1 inhibitor trials are caused by reduced cleavage of essential non-APP substrates rather than by reduced Aβ itself. Predictions: Substrate-selective BACE1 inhibitors that spare key non-APP substrates will show improved tolerability at Aβ-lowering doses.; Knockout of specific non-APP BACE1 substrates will recapitulate adverse phenotypes seen with broad BACE1 inhibition.; Severity of adverse effects will correlate with degree of non-APP substrate cleavage suppression rather than degree of Aβ reduction.",
